Package net.sourceforge.jeval.function

Interface Function

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    Abs, Acos, Asin, Atan, Atan2, Ceil, CharAt, CompareTo, CompareToIgnoreCase, Concat, Cos, EndsWith, Equals, EqualsIgnoreCase, Eval, Exp, Floor, IEEEremainder, IndexOf, LastIndexOf, Length, Log, Max, Min, Pow, Random, RegexMatches, Replace, Rint, Round, Sin, Split, Sqrt, StartsWith, Substring, Tan, TextLines, ToDegrees, ToLowerCase, ToRadians, ToUpperCase, Trim
    public interface Function
    A function that can be specified in an expression.

      • execute

        FunctionResult execute​(Evaluator evaluator,
                       java.lang.String arguments)
                throws FunctionException
        Executes the function for the specified argument. This method is called internally by Evaluator.
        Parameters:
        evaluator - An instance of Evaluator.
        arguments - The arguments that will be evaluated by the function. It is up to the function implementation to break the string into one or more arguments.
        Returns:
        The value of the evaluated argument and its type.
        Throws:
        FunctionException - thrown if the argument(s) are not valid for this function
